WEBVTT

00:01.349 --> 00:03.003
Previously on "Manifest"...

00:03.046 --> 00:05.918
I will go to the press
about everything.

00:05.962 --> 00:09.313
Our expenses just doubled.I know,
and I've got to get a job.

00:09.357 --> 00:11.402
I'm on it.
Dad,
what are you doing?

00:11.446 --> 00:13.317
I'm Danny.

00:13.361 --> 00:15.319
Thanks,
I can take it from here.

00:15.363 --> 00:17.452
Never mind.
I got this.

00:17.495 --> 00:19.715
Evie,
no you don't.

00:20.498 --> 00:22.239
Can you hear me?

00:22.283 --> 00:23.414
[ Indistinct conversation ]

00:23.458 --> 00:26.591
Our son is sick.

00:26.635 --> 00:29.681
He doesn't need you
to be a scientist right now.

00:29.725 --> 00:32.119
He needs you
to be his father.

00:32.162 --> 00:33.598
Jared:
Unified Dynamic Systems.

00:33.642 --> 00:37.646
Everything that I am coming
across points back to U.D.S.

00:37.689 --> 00:40.910
They are the ones who made
the passengers disappear.

00:40.953 --> 00:42.520
And I know
this sounds impossible,

00:42.564 --> 00:45.132
but Cal's fever,
I think it has something to do

00:45.175 --> 00:46.350
with what happened
on the plane.

00:46.394 --> 00:47.830
♪♪

00:47.873 --> 00:52.139
[ Indistinct announcement
over P.A. ]

00:52.182 --> 00:53.401
Really?

00:53.444 --> 00:55.664
What else could go wrong
on this flight?

00:55.707 --> 00:57.796
This flight
is not happening toyou.

00:57.840 --> 00:59.363
It's happening foryou.

00:59.407 --> 01:01.191
If it was happening
forme,

01:01.235 --> 01:03.541
it wouldn't have bumped me
from my original flight.

01:03.585 --> 01:05.804
Yet here you are.

01:05.848 --> 01:08.546
Now we're all
in this together.

01:08.590 --> 01:13.421
[ Indistinct announcement
over P.A. ]

01:18.382 --> 01:21.168
Hey, bud,
how you feeling?

01:21.211 --> 01:22.865
I'm scared.

01:23.909 --> 01:25.824
I still feel him.

01:25.868 --> 01:29.698
♪♪

01:29.741 --> 01:31.569
Marko?

01:31.613 --> 01:35.138
I think something bad
is gonna happen.

01:35.182 --> 01:36.400
♪♪

01:36.444 --> 01:38.402
To him and me.

01:38.446 --> 01:41.710
Hey,
I've got this.

01:41.753 --> 01:45.061
Okay?
I've got a plan.

01:45.105 --> 01:47.107
♪♪

01:47.150 --> 01:49.413
That's my boy.

01:49.457 --> 01:51.894
I want to go home.

01:51.937 --> 01:57.117
♪♪

01:57.160 --> 02:02.296
♪♪

02:02.339 --> 02:06.169
[ Engines roaring ]

02:06.213 --> 02:09.303
♪♪

02:09.346 --> 02:11.087
Hey!

02:11.131 --> 02:15.526
So, you are under doctor orders
to chill out all day.

02:15.570 --> 02:18.181
Okay.
Okay, and remember,
if you feel bad,

02:18.225 --> 02:19.922
your mom and dad
can call me any time.

02:22.446 --> 02:23.882
[ Laughs ]Come on.

02:23.926 --> 02:26.015
Let's get you a treat
before we get out of here.

02:26.058 --> 02:27.495
I'll meet you down.

02:30.541 --> 02:33.370
I wouldn't discharge him
if he wasn't better.

02:33.414 --> 02:34.589
Better enough
to go home,

02:34.632 --> 02:35.938
but he's not
out of the woods.

02:35.981 --> 02:38.245
He's still feeling Marko,
which means

02:38.288 --> 02:40.856
whatever happens to Marko
will happen to Cal.

02:40.899 --> 02:42.510
Seems like
the testing stopped.

02:42.553 --> 02:44.816
For now.
The passengers were moved.

02:44.860 --> 02:47.732
There's satellite footage
of the farm being torn down.

02:51.040 --> 02:53.347
But I know
how to find them.

02:53.390 --> 02:54.696
How do we do that?

02:54.739 --> 02:56.132
Follow the money.

02:56.176 --> 02:58.961
The farm was owned
by Unified Dynamic Systems.

02:59.004 --> 03:01.659
It turns out their
accounting firm is hiring,

03:01.703 --> 03:06.229
so I applied
for an entry-level job.

03:06.273 --> 03:07.709
Entry level?
Ben, you're way over-qualified.

03:07.752 --> 03:09.058
They're never
gonna hire you.

03:09.101 --> 03:10.973
Mr. Stone,
you seem much too qualified

03:11.016 --> 03:14.063
to be applying for...
Junior Revenue Accountant.

03:14.106 --> 03:16.674
JP Williamson
provides support

03:16.718 --> 03:19.242
for 35 Fortune 500 companies,
correct?

03:19.286 --> 03:20.548
That's correct.

03:20.591 --> 03:21.984
We work closely
with the likes of Boeing,

03:22.027 --> 03:24.116
AIG,
Unified Dynamic Systems...

03:24.160 --> 03:25.683
If I could
get in their books,

03:25.727 --> 03:27.511
I should be able
to follow the money trail

03:27.555 --> 03:29.731
from the farm
to wherever they're holding

03:29.774 --> 03:31.472
the missing
passengers now.

03:31.515 --> 03:32.734
And what better way
to service them

03:32.777 --> 03:35.519
by having someone
who is overqualified

03:35.563 --> 03:37.913
and starving to get back to work
on your team?

03:37.956 --> 03:40.220
It might work --
if they hire you.

03:40.263 --> 03:41.482
It has to work.

03:41.525 --> 03:43.788
Cal thinks
he's in danger.

03:43.832 --> 03:46.269
And he hasn't
been wrong yet.

03:46.313 --> 03:49.011
And it will cost you less
than hiring a guy

03:49.054 --> 03:51.927
who doesn't have
a 5 1/2-year gap on his résumé.

03:51.970 --> 03:53.276
[ Chuckles ]

03:53.320 --> 04:01.284
♪♪

04:01.328 --> 04:04.287
HR Rep: Welcome to
JP Williamson, Mr. Stone.Thank you.

04:04.331 --> 04:06.942
Thank you.

04:06.985 --> 04:10.119
I think this job
is gonna be great

04:10.162 --> 04:11.294
for all of us, Ben.

04:11.338 --> 04:13.818
Look, I know it's not
the ideal salary,

04:13.862 --> 04:16.168
but there's room
to grow, right?

04:16.212 --> 04:17.300
Yeah, yeah.

04:17.344 --> 04:18.910
And JP Williamson
handles the books

04:18.954 --> 04:20.564
for practically
half of corporate America.

04:20.608 --> 04:22.262
They have about
100,000 employees.

04:22.305 --> 04:24.046
And now my husband
is one of them.

04:24.089 --> 04:26.178
[ Chuckles ]
Olive: Yeah.
That'd be cool.

04:26.222 --> 04:27.397
Let me ask.

04:27.441 --> 04:30.052
Can I go
rock climbing today?

04:31.009 --> 04:33.316
Hmm, sounds awesome.
Wish I could go.

04:33.360 --> 04:37.146
Cool. Thanks.

04:38.582 --> 04:40.976
She seem off to you?

04:41.019 --> 04:43.239
Okay.
Full disclosure --

04:43.283 --> 04:46.634
She is going rock climbing
with Danny.

04:46.677 --> 04:48.940
Oh.
He asked me
if it would be okay.

04:48.984 --> 04:50.942
I was gonna
talk to you about it.

04:50.986 --> 04:52.335
It's something
that they started

04:52.379 --> 04:54.424
when she was getting off
her anti-depressants.

04:54.468 --> 04:55.730
It gave her a goal.

04:55.773 --> 04:56.992
They were
training weekly

04:57.035 --> 04:58.950
to hit a climb
in Acadia National Park,

04:58.994 --> 05:01.953
but listen, if you are
at all uncomfortable with it --

05:01.997 --> 05:03.868
No,
I think it's good.

05:03.912 --> 05:06.001
First day,
can't be late.

05:07.655 --> 05:09.613
Early shift?

05:09.657 --> 05:11.963
No, I got to
swing by Evie's.

05:12.007 --> 05:14.357
Glen called.
Beverly's not doing good.

05:14.401 --> 05:17.229
Oh, sorry to hear that.
Give her my best.

05:17.273 --> 05:18.753
Can we talk about
your plan?

05:18.796 --> 05:20.407
What if somebody
connected to the farm

05:20.450 --> 05:22.931
finds out
that you're snooping?How would they?

05:22.974 --> 05:25.716
It's the same as if I wanted
to snoop on a dirty cop

05:25.760 --> 05:26.935
by joining the company

05:26.978 --> 05:29.024
the N.Y.P.D.
outsources its payroll to.

05:29.067 --> 05:30.721
Dirty Harry
wouldn't have a clue.

05:30.765 --> 05:32.854
[ Scoffs ]
Okay, but you're a passenger.

05:32.897 --> 05:34.072
What if word gets out?

05:34.116 --> 05:35.900
They knew that
when they hired me.

05:35.944 --> 05:37.075
If they were suspicious,

05:37.119 --> 05:38.729
I wouldn't have
gotten the job.

05:38.773 --> 05:40.905
Still,
I'd keep a low profile.Of course.

05:40.949 --> 05:43.473
I'm just
gonna blend in.

05:43.517 --> 05:46.694
Flight 828
in the house!

05:46.737 --> 05:48.826
Benjamin Stone!

05:48.870 --> 05:51.263
What's going on, bro?

05:51.307 --> 05:52.743
Ronnie Wilcox?

05:52.787 --> 05:54.354
That's me, man!

05:54.397 --> 05:58.183
God, I can't believe
I'm supervising theBen Stone!

05:58.227 --> 05:59.707
Uh, this is for you.

05:59.750 --> 06:01.143
Can't get anywhere
in this place

06:01.186 --> 06:02.623
without
the company dog tags.

06:02.666 --> 06:04.538
Yeah, come on, man. Let me
give you the lay of the land --

06:04.581 --> 06:07.105
and, uh, maybe you can tell me
what it was like

06:07.149 --> 06:09.064
when you first met
the aliens, huh?

06:09.107 --> 06:11.545
They were nice.
Smelled great.

06:11.588 --> 06:13.155
Ha. Classic.

06:13.198 --> 06:15.636
So, uh, what clients
will I be involved with?

06:15.679 --> 06:16.811
Small bites, B. Stone.

06:16.854 --> 06:18.116
Tier 4 companies --

06:18.160 --> 06:20.162
the less-than-
$15 million-annually crew.

06:20.205 --> 06:22.904
Just a heads up --
my PhD in Applied Mathematics

06:22.947 --> 06:24.558
could be of use
for some of the big guns

06:24.601 --> 06:26.386
like Boeing,
U.D.S. --

06:26.429 --> 06:29.301
Tier-one companies are handled
by supervisors only --

06:29.345 --> 06:31.303
red security and all.

06:31.347 --> 06:32.783
It's a grind.

06:32.827 --> 06:34.219
We kiss their butts,

06:34.263 --> 06:36.918
spend half our time off-site
at their home offices...

06:36.961 --> 06:39.094
Well, I'd love
to tag along sometime,

06:39.137 --> 06:41.096
or if you need extra pair
of eyes while you work --

06:41.139 --> 06:43.577
Slow your roll,
B. Stone.

06:43.620 --> 06:45.927
Come on.
You just landed.

06:45.970 --> 06:48.320
Literally.
[ Chuckles ]

06:48.364 --> 06:50.801
Huh, this is you.

06:50.845 --> 06:52.281
Little welcoming gift
for you.

06:52.324 --> 06:53.761
[ Ben chuckles ]
Welcome.

06:53.804 --> 06:56.241
Oh, and, um,
I run a little poker game,

06:56.285 --> 06:58.548
middle limit,
you know, mostly our department,

06:58.592 --> 06:59.767
some logistics guys,
I.T.

06:59.810 --> 07:00.985
You know.

07:01.029 --> 07:02.813
Take over
the conference room,

07:02.857 --> 07:04.336
sling
a little company dirt.

07:04.380 --> 07:06.991
If you want,
no pressure, brah.

07:07.035 --> 07:08.602
I'll check
with my wife.

07:08.645 --> 07:10.081
Brah.
All right.

07:16.218 --> 07:19.134
[ Sighs ]

07:19.177 --> 07:29.144
♪♪

07:29.187 --> 07:34.192
♪♪

07:34.236 --> 07:36.456
[ Sighs ]

07:36.499 --> 07:40.677
[ Indistinct conversations,
keyboards clacking ]

07:40.721 --> 07:42.200
Glen:
Thanks for coming.

07:42.244 --> 07:44.507
Beverly could use
a friendly face.

07:44.551 --> 07:46.509
How is she?

07:46.553 --> 07:49.207
See for yourself.

07:49.251 --> 07:59.217
♪♪

07:59.261 --> 08:04.222
♪♪

08:04.266 --> 08:05.528
Hi, Beverly.

08:05.572 --> 08:06.834
Where's Evie?

08:06.877 --> 08:09.010
Sure is taking her
a long time to come home.

08:09.053 --> 08:11.012
I am sure
wherever she is now,

08:11.055 --> 08:13.188
she's okay.

08:13.231 --> 08:16.234
Will you sit with me
while I wait?

08:16.278 --> 08:18.019
♪♪

08:18.062 --> 08:20.543
Yeah,
of course I will.

08:20.587 --> 08:26.462
♪♪

08:26.506 --> 08:28.899
[ Cellphone clicks,
keyboard clacking ]

08:28.943 --> 08:30.640
[ Cellphone rings, beeps ]

08:30.684 --> 08:32.512
Hey,
you find something?

08:32.555 --> 08:33.861
Ben:
Not at first.

08:33.904 --> 08:36.690
My access was limited,
so I had to improvise.

08:36.733 --> 08:46.090
♪♪

08:46.134 --> 08:48.571
Funny how my ID
just stopped working.

08:48.615 --> 08:51.095
It gave me an excuse to borrow
one with greater access.

08:51.139 --> 08:53.837
Having trouble there,
my man?
Card...

08:53.881 --> 08:56.100
Luckily,
my boss is an 828 fanboy,

08:56.144 --> 08:57.928
so he was happy
to help.

08:57.972 --> 09:00.714
Borrow yours?
Sure.

09:00.757 --> 09:02.280
[ Keyboard clacking ]

09:02.324 --> 09:04.500
That got me
into the system.

09:04.544 --> 09:06.981
Saanvi:
And what did you find?

09:07.024 --> 09:08.765
Something called S.P.

09:08.809 --> 09:10.419
I couldn't get access.

09:10.462 --> 09:15.772
♪♪

09:15.816 --> 09:17.165
But here's
what I did get.

09:17.208 --> 09:19.341
You've been hearing about
Fiona Clarke, right?

09:19.384 --> 09:21.299
The big-shot professor
from the plane?

09:21.343 --> 09:23.650
Yeah, Her face shows up
in half the 828 news coverage.

09:23.693 --> 09:24.955
Why?

09:24.999 --> 09:26.174
Because she's working for

09:26.217 --> 09:27.784
whoever took
the missing passengers.

09:27.828 --> 09:33.181
♪♪

09:37.577 --> 09:40.536
Fiona Clarke started her career
in neural psychology,

09:40.580 --> 09:42.625
ended up being
blackballed in her field

09:42.669 --> 09:44.105
for her fringe beliefs,

09:44.148 --> 09:45.976
so she shifted to
spiritual circles and blew up.

09:46.020 --> 09:49.327
Huge online presence,
books, lectures.

09:49.371 --> 09:51.286
And that was before
we all disappeared.

09:51.329 --> 09:52.592
Fringe beliefs?
Like what?

09:52.635 --> 09:54.463
Like believing
all of our brains

09:54.506 --> 09:56.247
can sync up
to one another.

09:57.074 --> 09:59.468
Like Cal
and Marko Valeriev.

09:59.511 --> 10:01.426
Mm-hmm.

10:01.470 --> 10:05.387
It's all neural connectivity,
pathways.

10:05.430 --> 10:08.520
A computer alone at your home
is powerful,

10:08.564 --> 10:11.785
but one connected to a network
is all-powerful.

10:11.828 --> 10:15.049
The same could be said
of our brains.

10:15.092 --> 10:18.182
Networked brains.

10:18.226 --> 10:21.533
All her files
were marked S.P.

10:21.577 --> 10:22.970
I don't know
what that means,

10:23.013 --> 10:24.188
but it has to connect
to the detainees.

10:24.232 --> 10:27.191
I mean,
maybe she sold us out,

10:27.235 --> 10:28.758
had the passengers
abducted.

10:28.802 --> 10:30.499
Maybe she's the mastermind
behind what they're doing

10:30.542 --> 10:32.457
to the detainees
altogether.

10:32.501 --> 10:34.024
Hell,
maybe she's responsible

10:34.068 --> 10:36.853
for what happened
to the plane.

10:36.897 --> 10:38.550
Well,
you can ask her yourself.

10:38.594 --> 10:40.857
Tonight.

10:40.901 --> 10:47.734
♪♪

10:47.777 --> 10:50.301
Cal: [ Echoing]
No, not the red door!

10:50.345 --> 10:55.655
[ Speaking foreign language]

10:55.698 --> 11:02.792
♪♪

11:02.836 --> 11:04.098
Danny:
Killing it.

11:04.141 --> 11:05.752
Hey, did you crush
that soccer tournament

11:05.795 --> 11:08.493
like you're crushing
this climb?
Had to bail.

11:08.537 --> 11:11.888
It was like two days after
the plane came back.
Oh.

11:11.932 --> 11:13.890
I have another one
in a week.

11:13.934 --> 11:17.111
Nice.
Wish I could see it.

11:17.154 --> 11:20.810
♪♪

11:20.854 --> 11:22.725
Oh, damn it.

11:22.769 --> 11:24.422
It's all right.

11:24.466 --> 11:26.076
Next time,
make sure that your knee is bent

11:26.120 --> 11:27.556
before you reach.

11:27.599 --> 11:30.124
I don't want
to do this anymore.

11:30.167 --> 11:31.516
Well,
where'd that come from?

11:31.560 --> 11:33.475
This morning,
you seemed pumped to climb.

11:33.518 --> 11:35.999
Yeah,
and now I'm not.

11:36.043 --> 11:38.132
Olive,
talk to me.

11:38.175 --> 11:39.916
No.

11:39.960 --> 11:42.092
I'm out.

11:42.136 --> 11:44.138
Danny: Well, I'm not.

11:44.181 --> 11:46.575
I'll be here tomorrow.

11:46.618 --> 11:48.751
Why is
Ben Stone working

11:48.795 --> 11:51.493
a low-level accounting job
at JP Williamson?

11:51.536 --> 11:52.973
Maybe they need
the money.

11:53.016 --> 11:56.193
I think we've wasted enough time
on his paranoid theories.

11:56.237 --> 11:57.891
Yeah,
might not be paranoid.

11:57.934 --> 12:00.241
Every single law enforcement
and intelligence agency

12:00.284 --> 12:01.590
we've reached out to

12:01.633 --> 12:04.898
has zero information
on those missing passengers.

12:04.941 --> 12:06.334
Exactly.

12:06.377 --> 12:08.858
I think there's
an off-the-books, covert unit

12:08.902 --> 12:10.120
running the whole thing.

12:10.164 --> 12:11.818
We just don't know
who it is.

12:11.861 --> 12:13.950
That's what Stone
is trying to find out.

12:13.994 --> 12:15.517
And I'd bet my house

12:15.560 --> 12:17.867
he thinks he'll find the answer
at that accounting firm.

12:17.911 --> 12:20.478
Shouldn't we trust
our fellow agencies

12:20.522 --> 12:21.958
and not
some civilian?

12:22.002 --> 12:25.788
This civilian just might be
on to something.

12:25.832 --> 12:28.312
Hey, you free to come over
for dinner tonight?Man: Here you go.

12:28.356 --> 12:31.533
Lourdes would really like
to have you over.

12:31.576 --> 12:32.882
Might be good
for you

12:32.926 --> 12:35.755
to spend some time around
some friends for a change.

12:35.798 --> 12:38.670
Not sure that's a good idea
with everything going on.

12:38.714 --> 12:42.109
You being led by the voices
in your head to blow me off?

12:42.152 --> 12:44.285
No,
that's just me.

12:46.635 --> 12:49.769
Are you still
hearing them?

12:49.812 --> 12:51.422
The voices?

12:51.466 --> 12:52.989
I don't know,
but look, if you're worried

12:53.033 --> 12:55.383
about me messing up again,
it's not gonna happen, okay?

12:55.426 --> 12:56.863
At least not in a way
that affects you.

12:56.906 --> 13:01.781
It's you
that I'm worried about, Mick.

13:03.608 --> 13:05.088
The N.S.A.
is watching you.

13:05.132 --> 13:10.093
♪♪

13:10.137 --> 13:11.529
How do you know that?

13:11.573 --> 13:13.270
'Cause they've been
all over me,

13:13.314 --> 13:15.098
making sure I keep an eye
on you.

13:15.142 --> 13:16.796
I haven't
told them anything,

13:16.839 --> 13:19.015
and I never will.

13:19.059 --> 13:20.451
Thank you.

13:20.495 --> 13:22.584
Dispatcher:
All units be advised, 10-10.

13:22.627 --> 13:24.934
Shots fired
at Enrique's barbershop.

13:24.978 --> 13:26.849
Corner of Brooke and 20th.

13:26.893 --> 13:28.329
That's right around
the corner.
Yeah.

13:28.372 --> 13:29.765
[ Siren wails ]

13:29.809 --> 13:33.073
Detective Unit Three
in proximity and responding.

13:33.116 --> 13:35.858
[ Tires squeal ]

13:35.902 --> 13:37.729
[ Siren continues ]

13:37.773 --> 13:39.209
[ Tires screech ]

13:39.253 --> 13:40.820
Yo! Yo!

13:40.863 --> 13:43.257
Some tweaker just shot my uncle!
He ran off up the block!

13:43.300 --> 13:45.563
What'd he look like?He's got a red hoodie!
He was twitching like crazy!

13:45.607 --> 13:48.392
I'll call a bus.Where's your uncle?

13:48.436 --> 13:50.264
Oh, man,
Tío Enrique!

13:50.307 --> 13:52.309
Go get
some clean towels now.

13:52.353 --> 13:55.878
♪♪

13:55.922 --> 13:58.054
Do you have a pulse?!Not yet.

13:58.098 --> 13:59.751
Put pressure
on the wound.

13:59.795 --> 14:03.320
I told him to give the junkie
the money he wanted,

14:03.364 --> 14:05.496
but he wouldn't.

14:05.540 --> 14:07.194
What's happening?!

14:07.237 --> 14:09.892
What's happening?

14:09.936 --> 14:11.285
I-I don't know.

14:11.328 --> 14:12.590
I'm hearing a heartbeat,
but I'm not feeling a pulse.

14:12.634 --> 14:15.680
Enrique!
[ Speaking Spanish ]

14:15.724 --> 14:18.161
Come on.
Come on.

14:18.205 --> 14:20.860
Save him.
Save him.

14:20.903 --> 14:24.864
[ Crying ]

14:24.907 --> 14:27.127
No!

14:27.170 --> 14:29.869
No, Tío Enrique!

14:29.912 --> 14:32.132
No, no...

14:32.175 --> 14:34.699
[ Siren wails ]

14:34.743 --> 14:37.354
♪♪

14:42.142 --> 14:44.318
This was the last hot chocolate
in the break room.

14:44.361 --> 14:47.408
I'm gonna deny
I gave that to you, okay?

14:52.065 --> 14:55.895
Look, I don't understand
why he had to die.

14:57.113 --> 14:58.898
I'm sorry, Carlos.

14:58.941 --> 15:00.638
You guys were close?

15:00.682 --> 15:04.251
See, my uncle took me in
after my mother died.

15:04.294 --> 15:06.122
I was a sick little kid.

15:06.166 --> 15:07.950
I needed major surgery.

15:07.994 --> 15:09.909
I almost didn't make it.

15:09.952 --> 15:12.346
He helped me get better.

15:12.389 --> 15:14.739
You see,
the money he wouldn't give up,

15:14.783 --> 15:16.698
it was
to polish up the shop

15:16.741 --> 15:19.527
for me
to take over soon.

15:19.570 --> 15:22.182
He gave me a life.

15:22.225 --> 15:23.923
[ Crying ]

15:25.011 --> 15:28.144
I know what it's like
to lose somebody.

15:28.188 --> 15:31.626
You're destroyed,
like a building imploded.

15:32.453 --> 15:33.758
But one day, slowly,

15:33.802 --> 15:36.544
you will start
to build yourself back up,

15:36.587 --> 15:37.937
brick by brick.

15:37.980 --> 15:39.634
You finished building?

15:39.677 --> 15:42.942
Not even close.

15:44.944 --> 15:48.077
[ Door opens ]

15:48.121 --> 15:57.173
♪♪

15:57.217 --> 15:59.306
[ Door closes ]

15:59.349 --> 16:00.916
♪♪

16:00.960 --> 16:03.397
It's okay.
Take your time.

16:03.440 --> 16:13.015
♪♪

16:13.059 --> 16:15.278
I can't do it.

16:15.322 --> 16:17.454
Yes, you can.

16:17.498 --> 16:20.066
Carlos, this man is dangerous,
a killer.

16:20.109 --> 16:22.633
We're still coming up short
on the weapon,

16:22.677 --> 16:26.289
so he'll do it again
if you don't stop him.

16:26.333 --> 16:27.551
This is the only way

16:27.595 --> 16:29.510
you're gonna get justice
for your uncle.

16:29.553 --> 16:33.035
♪♪

16:33.079 --> 16:34.863
[ Sighs ]

16:36.169 --> 16:38.519
People freeze up.

16:38.562 --> 16:41.043
Panic.
Which one was it?

16:41.087 --> 16:42.175
Second from the right.

16:42.218 --> 16:43.785
No one's processing
his release tonight.

16:43.828 --> 16:45.395
We'll talk to Carlos
in the morning,

16:45.439 --> 16:48.094
and hopefully,
he'll turn.

16:48.137 --> 16:50.357
Yeah, hopefully.

16:50.400 --> 16:53.142
What is it?
I...

16:53.186 --> 16:54.404
I don't know.

16:54.448 --> 16:55.623
There's something
about this kid.

16:55.666 --> 16:58.234
I need
to help him.

17:00.106 --> 17:01.411
Have a good night.

17:01.455 --> 17:03.631
Jared: Did you forget
about dinner?

17:03.674 --> 17:04.849
[ Sighs ]

17:04.893 --> 17:06.851
I already told Lourdes
you're in.

17:09.724 --> 17:12.074
[ Cellphone chimes ]

17:12.118 --> 17:15.077
[ Sighs ]

17:27.437 --> 17:29.570
Saanvi:
Mirror neurons?

17:29.613 --> 17:31.093
This is heavy stuff.

17:31.137 --> 17:33.313
No one really knows
the extent

17:33.356 --> 17:35.184
of how
these cells operate.

17:35.228 --> 17:37.969
[ Applause ]

17:38.013 --> 17:42.191
[ Soft music plays]

17:42.235 --> 17:44.759
Your beating heart.

17:44.802 --> 17:47.109
My beating heart.

17:47.153 --> 17:48.806
We're all one.

17:54.421 --> 17:56.988
Honey, we're home.

17:58.120 --> 18:00.340
The kitchen
is a disaster area.

18:00.383 --> 18:01.558
Do not go in there.

18:01.602 --> 18:04.126
It smells great.

18:04.170 --> 18:06.302
Lourdes: Hi.

18:10.219 --> 18:14.658
All right, well, uh,
I'll go change my clothes.

18:16.007 --> 18:17.748
Oh, my God,
I'm so sorry.

18:17.792 --> 18:19.054
I forgot
to bring anything.

18:19.098 --> 18:21.143
Dude,
you're not a guest.

18:21.187 --> 18:22.666
You're family.

18:26.366 --> 18:27.758
♪♪

18:27.802 --> 18:29.760
Jared tells me

18:29.804 --> 18:32.633
that this invitation
was weirding you out.

18:32.676 --> 18:33.938
Weird?

18:33.982 --> 18:35.940
No, what's weird
about this?

18:35.984 --> 18:38.552
Still the worst
liar ever.

18:38.595 --> 18:41.468
[ Sighs ]

18:41.511 --> 18:43.774
We're gonna push through.

18:43.818 --> 18:45.559
[ Laughter ]

18:45.602 --> 18:47.169
He dunked it
from the free-throw line.

18:47.213 --> 18:48.692
I can't believe you're such
a die-hard Knicks fan.

18:48.736 --> 18:49.998
[ Laughs ]

18:50.041 --> 18:51.826
I'm sorry. What can I say?
I'm loyal.

18:51.869 --> 18:53.001
After 5 1/2 years,

18:53.044 --> 18:54.959
the one thing
that's still the same

18:55.003 --> 18:56.265
is the Knicks suck.[ Laughs ]

18:56.309 --> 18:57.658
Hey, why don't you have
a little bit?

18:57.701 --> 18:59.268
I'm good.I'll have some.

18:59.312 --> 19:02.619
I, um, I haven't had a drink
since that night, so...

19:02.663 --> 19:04.621
Michaela,
you're not an alcoholic.

19:04.665 --> 19:06.101
You're allowed to have
a glass of wine.

19:06.145 --> 19:08.190
No one's looking. I'mlooking.

19:08.234 --> 19:10.236
Way to be a pillbox.

19:10.279 --> 19:13.282
[ Laughs ]
Wait,
where do I know that from?

19:13.326 --> 19:16.242
[ Laughing ] That was
Evie's favorite insult.

19:16.285 --> 19:17.765
No, no, no.

19:17.808 --> 19:20.115
Her favorite insult
was bitch-monkey.Bitch-monkey.

19:20.159 --> 19:22.204
[ Gasps ]
Oh, Bobby Tufford.

19:22.248 --> 19:23.727
Oh, 6th grade,

19:23.771 --> 19:26.165
Evie shows up to school
in heels, because she's Evie,

19:26.208 --> 19:29.516
so Bobby Tufford decides
to write "slut" on her locker.

19:29.559 --> 19:30.778
Ouch.

19:30.821 --> 19:32.388
Evie catches him
in the act,

19:32.432 --> 19:34.912
but when Mrs. Springs asks her
who wrote it,

19:34.956 --> 19:37.045
Evie doesn't
rat Bobby out.

19:37.088 --> 19:40.788
She waits until after school,
calls him a bitch-monkey,

19:40.831 --> 19:43.617
and then beats the crap
out of him.

19:43.660 --> 19:45.706
[ Laughter ]She didn't want justice.

19:45.749 --> 19:47.577
She wanted revenge.

19:47.621 --> 19:48.796
Sounds like she got it.

19:48.839 --> 19:50.711
Mm. [ Laughs ]

19:50.754 --> 19:52.930
[ Heart beating]

19:52.974 --> 19:54.628
What's wrong,
Mick?

19:54.671 --> 19:57.718
[ Heart beating]

19:57.761 --> 20:00.242
I have to go.

20:00.286 --> 20:01.983
Really?
I-I have ice cream.

20:02.026 --> 20:04.464
This was really nice, you guys.
Thank you so much.

20:07.380 --> 20:09.947
[ Door opens, closes ]

20:11.427 --> 20:13.951
Hey, we tried.

20:13.995 --> 20:16.040
She wasn't ready.

20:19.218 --> 20:22.699
[ Horns honking ]

20:26.616 --> 20:29.837
Carlos, open up.

20:32.796 --> 20:35.277
What do you want?

20:35.321 --> 20:37.018
Same thing
that I wanted earlier --

20:37.061 --> 20:38.802
positive ID
on your uncle's killer.

20:38.846 --> 20:40.282
I told you
I wasn't sure.

20:40.326 --> 20:42.284
Yeah, you also said that
you don't think you saw a gun.

20:42.328 --> 20:43.285
'Cause I didn't.

20:43.329 --> 20:44.939
We didn't find a gun,
Carlos,

20:44.982 --> 20:46.810
because you
found it first.

20:46.854 --> 20:49.117
You stashed it away,
failed to make an ID.

20:49.160 --> 20:51.293
Soon enough, that perp's
back out on the street,

20:51.337 --> 20:54.078
at which point you take him out
with his own gun.

20:54.905 --> 20:57.125
You got no proof.

20:57.168 --> 20:58.257
No, I don't.

20:58.300 --> 20:59.606
I also don't have
a search warrant,

20:59.649 --> 21:00.824
but I could get one.

21:00.868 --> 21:02.130
And if something happens,

21:02.173 --> 21:04.567
I now have
a primary suspect.

21:04.611 --> 21:06.743
Don't do this.

21:06.787 --> 21:08.484
Don't throw your life away
for revenge.

21:08.528 --> 21:09.920
What life?

21:09.964 --> 21:11.139
I'm all alone.

21:11.182 --> 21:13.272
I know that feeling,
okay?

21:13.315 --> 21:15.186
I also know
what it's like

21:15.230 --> 21:18.277
to take someone's life
because I did by accident.

21:18.320 --> 21:21.018
It haunts me
every single day.

21:21.062 --> 21:23.151
I can't even imagine
what it would be like

21:23.194 --> 21:25.109
to do that
on purpose.

21:27.895 --> 21:30.114
Fiona:
Imagine if we could empathize

21:30.158 --> 21:36.033
not only with those we know
but with everyone.

21:36.077 --> 21:37.426
Would wars end?

21:37.470 --> 21:39.123
Would -- Would poverty?

21:39.167 --> 21:41.517
The potential is boundless

21:41.561 --> 21:47.044
and our best hope to fend off
the looming threat of A.I.

21:47.088 --> 21:50.047
When we learn
how to harness the power

21:50.091 --> 21:55.531
of collective consciousness
with the Mirror Factor --

21:55.575 --> 21:59.187
Checkmate.

21:59.230 --> 22:02.538
♪♪

22:02.582 --> 22:04.018
Finally.

22:04.061 --> 22:06.803
I've been waiting for you.

22:06.847 --> 22:16.247
♪♪

22:22.166 --> 22:25.866
We've certainly generated
plenty of notoriety.

22:25.909 --> 22:27.215
I imagine we could all
go on tour.

22:27.258 --> 22:29.217
Thanks for waiting.Speaking of,

22:29.260 --> 22:30.697
you said that
you were waiting for us.

22:30.740 --> 22:31.959
What did you mean
by that?

22:32.002 --> 22:33.787
In the wake
of any traumatic event,

22:33.830 --> 22:35.223
it's inevitable

22:35.266 --> 22:36.790
the participants
eventually seek each other out.

22:36.833 --> 22:40.097
So, it has nothing to do
with you experiencing a calling.

22:40.141 --> 22:41.795
I'm sorry,
a-a calling?

22:41.838 --> 22:43.274
That's our own shorthand

22:43.318 --> 22:45.233
for some of the visions
and voices

22:45.276 --> 22:47.322
some of the passengers
have been receiving.

22:47.366 --> 22:49.803
Have they, indeed?Why don't you
just tell us

22:49.846 --> 22:51.152
exactly how
you're involved

22:51.195 --> 22:52.414
with the government
secretly detaining

22:52.458 --> 22:54.242
11 passengers
from our flight.

22:55.069 --> 22:57.941
Forgive my abundance
of ignorance,

22:57.985 --> 22:59.595
but detained passengers?

22:59.639 --> 23:00.857
Detained when?

23:00.901 --> 23:03.120
There are 11 people
from our flight

23:03.164 --> 23:04.600
who still remain
unaccounted for.

23:04.644 --> 23:06.602
Who we think are being
experimented on.

23:06.646 --> 23:08.952
It's being tracked
in a classified database

23:08.996 --> 23:10.780
with your name
all over it.

23:10.824 --> 23:12.303
Who are
you working for?

23:12.347 --> 23:15.306
And what does the Mirror Factor
have to do with it all?

23:15.350 --> 23:17.483
♪♪

23:17.526 --> 23:19.963
Well, uh...

23:20.007 --> 23:21.574
Four days
after we returned,

23:21.617 --> 23:23.314
I was approached
by a non-profit

23:23.358 --> 23:26.796
interested in funding
my mind-body research.

23:26.840 --> 23:29.364
They put me
on retainer,

23:29.408 --> 23:31.453
underwrote
tonight's lecture.

23:31.497 --> 23:34.456
No one mentioned a word
about government affiliation,

23:34.500 --> 23:37.024
let alone
d-detained passengers.

23:37.067 --> 23:38.504
What's
the non-profit called?

23:38.547 --> 23:40.375
The Singularity Project.

23:40.419 --> 23:42.333
S.P.

23:42.377 --> 23:45.249
It's time
to go play some poker.

23:45.293 --> 23:47.774
It could be my way into
the Singularity Project.

23:47.817 --> 23:51.342
Ronnie: That's the river card,
and it's down to two.

23:51.386 --> 23:53.562
We got Passenger Ben Stone,

23:53.606 --> 23:55.477
fresh from
his alien abduction...

23:55.521 --> 23:56.696
[ Laughter ]

23:56.739 --> 23:58.654
...and David James,

23:58.698 --> 24:03.006
an insignificantly small cog
in the I.T. machinery.

24:03.050 --> 24:04.878
I'm sorry
you got to work with him.

24:04.921 --> 24:06.619
Thank you,
thank you.

24:06.662 --> 24:08.577
Think too long,
you think wrong.

24:08.621 --> 24:10.231
Ooh.
He calls.

24:10.274 --> 24:11.667
All right,
let's see them.

24:11.711 --> 24:13.277
Turn them,
same time.

24:14.104 --> 24:16.498
Oh!

24:16.542 --> 24:18.631
And Ben takes it!Come on.

24:18.674 --> 24:20.546
Poker's a game of probability.
Math helps me.

24:20.589 --> 24:22.286
Oh, another accounting guy
that thinks I.T.

24:22.330 --> 24:24.071
is less rigorous
than math.

24:24.114 --> 24:25.072
Dude, not at all.

24:25.115 --> 24:26.421
In fact,

24:26.465 --> 24:28.249
I can't imagine handling
all that data coming in.

24:28.292 --> 24:30.338
You know, the security,
the storage.

24:30.381 --> 24:32.514
Some respect,
finally.

24:32.558 --> 24:35.212
Hey, you should see
some of these raw data dumps

24:35.256 --> 24:36.518
from these
massive companies.

24:36.562 --> 24:39.347
It's incomprehensible,
but trippy.

24:39.390 --> 24:41.523
I'd like to, actually.
Hook me up.

24:41.567 --> 24:42.916
All right.

24:42.959 --> 24:44.700
♪♪

24:44.744 --> 24:47.747
Hey.
How was the climb?

24:47.790 --> 24:49.662
I quit.

24:50.924 --> 24:52.752
It's too hard.

24:52.795 --> 24:55.711
Too hard?

24:55.755 --> 24:57.147
Huh.

24:57.191 --> 25:00.890
Well, harder than riding down
Tait Hill with no hands?

25:00.934 --> 25:02.109
You busted your lip
three times.

25:02.152 --> 25:03.414
You didn't quit
until you nailed it.

25:03.458 --> 25:05.547
How do you remember
stuff like that?

25:05.591 --> 25:07.680
I'm your dad.
I remember everything.

25:07.723 --> 25:08.898
[ Chuckles ]

25:08.942 --> 25:12.075
Your mom told me
climbing really helped you

25:12.119 --> 25:15.296
when things
weren't going so good.

25:15.339 --> 25:17.690
Well, that's a polite way
of putting it.

25:17.733 --> 25:20.693
I'm just saying,
you're great now,

25:20.736 --> 25:25.088
so I'm a big fan
of whatever got you here, okay?

25:25.132 --> 25:26.655
Okay.

25:26.699 --> 25:28.527
[ Both chuckle ]

25:28.570 --> 25:29.919
[ Chuckles ]

25:29.963 --> 25:32.052
Thank you,
Dad.

25:32.095 --> 25:33.706
Ben:
Hey, bud. Doing okay?

25:33.749 --> 25:36.056
You want me to bring you
some breakfast upstairs?

25:36.099 --> 25:37.927
I feel him
even more now.

25:37.971 --> 25:40.190
♪♪

25:40.234 --> 25:43.150
That man -- things are
getting worse for him.

25:43.193 --> 25:44.499
♪♪

25:44.543 --> 25:47.589
Listen,
last night I found out a secret,

25:47.633 --> 25:50.331
and that secret
makes us so close

25:50.374 --> 25:53.029
to finding Marko
and making him safe.

25:53.073 --> 25:54.988
We're so close, Cal.

25:55.031 --> 25:56.642
We're so close.

25:56.685 --> 25:58.078
♪♪

25:58.121 --> 26:01.777
[ Indistinct conversations,
police radio chatter ]

26:01.821 --> 26:03.300
You okay?

26:03.344 --> 26:05.564
You ran out of dinner
pretty fast last night.

26:05.607 --> 26:07.043
I had a thought
on the case,

26:07.087 --> 26:10.351
and I wanted
to follow up.

26:10.394 --> 26:14.747
So, that thought
on our case was?

26:17.837 --> 26:19.403
Carlos is planning
a revenge kill,

26:19.447 --> 26:20.970
and I think
he still has the gun.

26:21.014 --> 26:22.842
Possible.
Let's get a warrant.

26:22.885 --> 26:24.278
I went there
last night.

26:24.321 --> 26:25.627
Please tell me
you did not conduct

26:25.671 --> 26:27.194
an unwarranted search
for that gun.

26:27.237 --> 26:28.543
No,
I just asked him about it.

26:28.587 --> 26:31.154
Oh, you askedhim.
How'd that go?

26:31.981 --> 26:34.288
I think
he'll come around.
[ Scoffs ]

26:34.331 --> 26:36.072
So much
for pulling a warrant.

26:36.116 --> 26:37.639
You realize
if he had that gun,

26:37.683 --> 26:39.598
it's long gone by now.
You realize that, right?

26:39.641 --> 26:40.990
See, this is
what I'm talking about.

26:41.034 --> 26:43.210
Those voices in your head
getting in the way,

26:43.253 --> 26:45.212
making you go s--

26:45.255 --> 26:46.605
♪♪

26:46.648 --> 26:49.216
Jared:
I'll be damned.

26:49.259 --> 26:56.615
♪♪

26:56.658 --> 26:58.094
I'm ready.

26:58.138 --> 27:02.664
♪♪

27:02.708 --> 27:04.623
Diaz, we're ready
to make the ID.

27:04.666 --> 27:05.798
Love to help you
with that,

27:05.841 --> 27:07.495
but your suspect's
been cut loose.

27:07.538 --> 27:09.976
Needed the cell.
We had nothing on him, guys.

27:10.019 --> 27:12.108
Couldn't keep him forever.

27:12.152 --> 27:16.069
♪♪

27:16.112 --> 27:22.075
♪♪

27:22.118 --> 27:25.774
Hey,
you ready to try again?

27:25.818 --> 27:27.254
[ Sighs ]

27:27.297 --> 27:28.908
I thought
you might've bailed.

27:28.951 --> 27:30.431
I said I'd be here.

27:30.474 --> 27:32.476
I'll never lie
to you.

27:32.520 --> 27:34.696
Ilied to you.

27:34.740 --> 27:38.700
I never wanted to climb Acadia
or anything.

27:38.744 --> 27:40.093
♪♪

27:40.136 --> 27:42.748
So why did you train
so hard?

27:42.791 --> 27:44.619
♪♪

27:44.663 --> 27:47.927
Because I like
spending time with you.

27:47.970 --> 27:50.233
Back at ya.

27:50.277 --> 27:52.975
And it's no big deal.
Forget Acadia.

27:53.019 --> 27:55.108
No, we're doing it.

27:55.151 --> 27:56.370
Excuse me?

27:56.413 --> 27:58.459
I'm not a quitter,

27:58.502 --> 28:01.244
and I'm pretty good
at this.

28:01.288 --> 28:03.116
Eh, you're okay.

28:03.159 --> 28:05.292
[ Both chuckle ]Well,
what are we waiting for?

28:05.335 --> 28:07.163
Let's do it.
Okay.

28:07.207 --> 28:09.339
Hey!
'Sup, Stone?

28:09.383 --> 28:10.732
[ Laughs ]

28:10.776 --> 28:13.213
I am gonna need like six
of these to offset last night.

28:13.256 --> 28:14.736
[ Laughs ] Nice.

28:14.780 --> 28:17.130
Hey, super excited to show you
our sequence systems.

28:17.173 --> 28:18.740
I'm excited
to nerd out on it.

28:18.784 --> 28:21.612
I actually took some
computer science in college.

28:21.656 --> 28:23.832
Oh!
I'm -- I'm so --
I'm so sorry.

28:23.876 --> 28:25.878
It's okay.
It's, uh, not that hot.

